                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.1D1/51: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-15T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 15, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>379. Your 523, November 13, 7 p.m. Department approves the first sentence of your
                    proposed statement but feels that the second sentence thereof should be omitted.
                    Department prefers to avoid any suggestion which might lead to the conclusion
                    that a Convention excepting the individual States would be more acceptable to
                    this Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
